params.borrows: The total borrows of the asset in the market

getSupplyRate(address,uint256,uint256).details: The return value should be scaled by 1e18, thus a return value of     `(true, 1000000000000)` implies an interest rate of 0.000001 or 0.0001% *per block*.

params.asset: The asset to get the interest rate of
params.borrows: The total borrows of the asset in the market
params.cash: The total cash of the asset in the market

getSupplyRate(address,uint256,uint256).return: Success or failure and the supply interest rate per block scaled by 10e18

params.borrows: The amount of borrows in the market
params.cash: The amount of cash in the market
params.reserveFactorMantissa: The current reserve factor for the market
params.reserves: The amount of reserves in the market

getSupplyRate(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.return: The supply rate percentage per block as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)

params.baseRatePerYear: The approximate target base APR, as a mantissa (scaled by 1e18)
params.jumpMultiplierPerYear: The multiplierPerBlock after hitting a specified utilization point
params.kink_: The utilization point at which the jump multiplier is applied
params.multiplierPerYear: The rate of increase in interest rate wrt utilization (scaled by 1e18)

params.borrows: The amount of borrows in the market
params.cash: The amount of cash in the market
params.reserves: The amount of reserves in the market (currently unused)

utilizationRate(uint256,uint256,uint256).return: The utilization rate as a mantissa between [0, 1e18]

getBorrowRate(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Gets the current borrow interest rate based on the given asset, total cash and total borrows

getBorrowRate(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Calculates the current borrow rate per block, with the error code expected by the market

getSupplyRate(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Gets the current supply interest rate based on the given asset, total cash and total borrows

getSupplyRate(uint256,uint256,uint256,ui.notice: Calculates the current supply rate per block

updateJumpRateModel(uint256,uint256,uint.notice: Update the parameters of the interest rate model (only callable by owner, i.e. Timelock)

utilizationRate(uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: Calculates the utilization rate of the market: `borrows / (cash + borrows - reserves)`
